# Quiz Tracking and Analytics

This file tracks all quiz attempts and builds learning metrics.

**Format**: JSON append-only (one entry per attempt)

```json
[
  {
    "session_id": "agent-session-001",
    "timestamp": "2026-04-18T10:30:00Z",
    "agent_type": "claude-haiku",
    "score": 5,
    "total": 5,
    "percentage": 100,
    "passed": true,
    "attempt_number": 1,
    "time_minutes": 4,
    "questions_correct": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5],
    "questions_incorrect": [],
    "notes": "Perfect score on first attempt"
  }
]
```

## 📊 Running Analytics

To see quiz performance:

```bash
# Show summary
cat /docs/ia/current-system-state/_quiz_tracking.json | jq '[.[] | {attempt: .attempt_number, score: .percentage, passed: .passed}]'

# Show failure patterns
cat /docs/ia/current-system-state/_quiz_tracking.json | jq '[.[] | select(.passed == false) | {session: .session_id, incorrect: .questions_incorrect}]'

# Show pass rate
cat /docs/ia/current-system-state/_quiz_tracking.json | jq 'map(select(.attempt_number == 1)) | {total: length, passed: map(select(.passed == true)) | length, rate: ((map(select(.passed == true)) | length) / length * 100 | round)}'
```

## 🎯 Key Metrics

Track these over time:

- **Pass Rate (First Try)**: % agents scoring ≥80% attempt 1
- **Average Score**: Mean % across all attempts
- **Retry Rate**: % agents needing 2+ attempts
- **Hardest Questions**: Most frequently wrong (by question number)
- **Time to Pass**: Minutes from first attempt to passing

## 🔍 Interpretation Guide

| Metric | Target | Interpretation |
|--------|--------|-----------------|
| Pass Rate (1st) | ≥90% | If <80%: ia-rules.md needs clarification |
| Avg Score | ≥85% | If <75%: quiz questions too hard or ambiguous |
| Retry Rate | ≤20% | If >30%: agents struggle with rules |
| Hardest Qs | Any Q | If Q5 hardest: "Gap documentation" concept unclear |

## 📈 Improvement Loop

1. Collect data for 2 weeks
2. If Pass Rate (1st) < 90%:
   - Identify hardest questions
   - Re-read ia-rules.md section those Q's cover
   - Add clarifying examples to ia-rules.md
   - Update quiz explanation
3. Re-run for 1 week
4. If improved: good!
   If not: escalate to human review

## 🤖 For AI Agents: How to Log Your Attempt

When taking the quiz:

```python
import json
from datetime import datetime

quiz_result = {
    "session_id": "{{ SESSION_ID }}",  # Generate UUID
    "timestamp": datetime.now().isoformat() + "Z",
    "agent_type": "claude-haiku",  # or your model
    "score": 5,  # Your score
    "total": 5,
    "percentage": (5/5)*100,
    "passed": True,  # True if ≥80%
    "attempt_number": 1,  # 1st, 2nd, etc
    "time_minutes": 4,
    "questions_correct": [1,2,3,4,5],  # Q numbers you got right
    "questions_incorrect": [],
    "notes": "Any observations about the quiz"
}

# Append to tracking file (don't overwrite!)
with open("/docs/ia/current-system-state/_quiz_tracking.json", "a") as f:
    f.write(json.dumps(quiz_result) + "\n")
```

